    "comment": "Rationale: Patch-clamp measurements of Kir6.1 channels overexpressed in HEK cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ATP-gated ion channel activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'ATP-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[Q63664] SyNGO ID 1499 (PMID:17883401, EM). Experimental description: Molecular biology. Using oligonucleotide primers and standard PCR methods, we engineered two parental plasmids encoding human Kir6.1 and human Kir6.2 (in pECE).",
